What you need to know:

Stephen Curry led a balanced offence with a game-high 32 points as the Golden State Warriors beat Nikola Jokic's Denver Nuggets 118-97.The 30-point game was the 12th in Curry's past 13 outings. He was held to just 18 points in a four-point loss at Washington on Wednesday.Kelly Oubre had 23 points, Andrew Wiggins 19, Jordan Poole 15 as the under-manned Warriors surprised the Nuggets.